<doc id="724381" wikidata="Q6629035" url="?curid=724381" title="List of mosques in Lahore">
<text>This is a list of mosques in the city of Lahore, Pakistan. This city has remained capital of Delhi Sultanate and Mughal Empire at various times, thus hosting multiple mosques from that era.

==Pre Mughal Mosques==

* Neevin Mosque, 1460 CE

==Mughal Mosques==

* Begum Shahi Mosque, 1614 CE 
* Dai Anga Mosque, 1635 CE
* Moti Mosque, 1635 CE
* Wazir Khan Mosque, 1642 CE
* Badshahi Mosque, 1673 CE
* Suneri Mosque, 1753 CE
* Shaheed Ganj Mosque, 1753 CE
* Oonchi Mosque
==Post Independence Mosques==
* Grand Jamia Mosque, Lahore, 2014 
* Data Durbar Complex, 1978 CE
* Shab Bhar Mosque, 1917 
* Shia Mosque
* Jamia Mosque Qudas Ahlehadees, Lahore

==See also==

* Temples in Lahore

